, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'S=
egoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; l=
ine-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>D=
oubling Down on Our Minds</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>If there&#8217;s one=
 key message I want you to take away from reading this, it&#8217;s that </s=
pan><strong>new knowledge transfer technologies unlock new and better ways =
of thinking.</strong><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Human brains are not =
static; they&#8217;re dynamic, and capable of improving. New technologies c=
an spur those improvements. The phonetic alphabet and the printing press di=
dn&#8217;t just help spread ideas, they made us smarter in the process. Whi=
le we&#8217;re still early in the development of AI, chess and Go provide e=
arly proof points that we&#8217;re not done improving.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D=
"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><=
span>Genetic evolution is a slow process, but our minds haven&#8217;t evolv=
ed through genetics alone for millennia. As Daniel Dennett highlights in </=
span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/97fa1148-4c30-4332-8a17-1=
487ba77bd7f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">From Ba=
cteria to Bach and Back</a></em><span>, our brains have coevolved with meme=
s, &#8220;</span><em>words striving to reproduce</em><span>.&#8221; New inf=
ormation &#8211; new words, ideas, arguments, images &#8211; can be &#8220;=
downloaded to your necktop,&#8221; where it mixes and mashes with all of th=
e other memes you&#8217;ve downloaded and becomes part of your personal rea=
soning capabilities.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Phonetic language, the print=
ing press, and AI serve to distribute memes further and faster, so that we =
can upgrade our minds and provide fresh new insights.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"=
color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">De=
nnett addresses AI directly in the closing paragraphs of his 2017 book, wri=
ting:&nbsp;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin:=
 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>Or we may cont=
inue to thrive, in an environment we have created with the help of artifact=
s that do most of the heavy cognitive lifting their own way, in an age of p=
ost-intelligent design. There is not just coevolution between memes and gen=
es; there is codependence between our minds&#8217; top-down reasoning abili=
ties and the bottom-up uncomprehending talents of our animal brains. And if=
 our future follows the trajectory of our past &#8212; something that is pa=
rtly in our control &#8211; </span><strong>our artificial intelligences wil=
l continue to be dependent on us even as we become more warily dependent on=
 them</strong><span>.</span></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: #40404=
0; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This separation=
 of powers and codependence is what I&#8217;m talking about. It mirrors the=
 phonetic alphabet and the printing press. Give them more of the heavy cogn=
itive lifting so that we might focus on our minds&#8217; top-down reasoning=
 abilities, on the rare and novel sparks of insight that people like Anaxim=
ander were able to conjure.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I don&#8217;t know what thos=
e insights will be. What I do know, what I have a strong human intuition ab=
out, at least, is that if we are at the foot of one of these technological/=
human insight-powered turning points, people are going to spend a lot of ti=
me and effort training their minds in order to generate those insights.&nbs=
p;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">Far from giving up on learning because AI is smarter than u=
s, pushing our brains is only going to get more popular, and we&#8217;re on=
ly going to get better, just like we did in chess and Go.&nbsp;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">By pushing what AI can do and learning how it thinks, we&#8217;ll learn m=
ore about how our own minds work, and what makes them unique.&nbsp;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;"><span>We&#8217;ll come up with wild theories, like this one </span><a=
 href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/7a3ef58a-caa7-4b57-9ba2-51d9098a218d=
?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D=
"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">from Kevin Kelly</=
a><span> &#8211; &#8220;That our brains tend to produce dreams at all times=
, and that during waking hours, our brains tame the dream machine into perc=
eption and truthiness.&#8221; He came up with it while playing with generat=
ive AI, by noticing similarities between AI&#8217;s hallucinations and our =
dreams and making a uniquely human leap based on his intuition.&nbsp;</span=
></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;">Wild theories based on facts, experience, and intuition (whi=
ch we&#8217;ll then subject to the scientific method, of course) will be at=
 a premium. I suspect that we&#8217;re going to see an explosion in the pop=
ularity of things like meditation, breathwork, psychedelics, lucid dreaming=
, ongoing education, sleep, nootropics, writing, walks in nature, tutoring,=
 exercise, alcohol-cutting, in-person group experiences, debates, and all s=
orts of ways that might assist in their creation.</p><p style=3D"color: #40=
